summary: An Ordinance authorizing and directing the City Comptroller, to advertise for sale negotiable bonds of the City of Seattle, in the sum of One Hundred Thousand Dollars ($100,000.00); of bonds in the sum of Eight Hundred Thousand Dollars ($800,000.00), authorized, ratified and voted at a special election held in the City of Seattle, on the 29th day of December, 1908, under and pursuant to provisions of Ordinance No. 19605; and declaring an emergency.
